reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this bookcase despite the reviews for the affordability and ease of assembly. It was a bit time consuming to put together but once I got it set up it wasn't too bad. If you are thinking about purchasing this I would say to be sure to have a mallet on hand to hammer in the poles to the plastic attachments because this is what will help to ensure it is more secure. The set doesn't come preequiped with tools so be sure to have at least a mallet handy. Also be careful with the paper film because it can tear easily since it is quite cheap. I also had some clear construction adhesive gorilla glue as there were a couple of the films that had rips in them I took the glue and layered a thin layer across the bottom where the tear was and let it dry. Additionally, if you intend to place large books in this case I would suggest lying them flat so that there isn't too much weight being applied to the film (remember this is Literally a Cheap case) so don't expect too much for the price. Overall it took me two hours to put it together and I took my time. These are photos of it the next day prior to me adding the books in it and to be honest it is sturdy but AGAIN I used a mallet during the installation process. This review is lengthy but I hope it is beneficial to helping someone during making their purchase. Happy Shopping. 😊Update: I uploaded a couple of photos of the books being added to the book case just for a better visual.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good Buy for the Price
reviews.reviewText: I wasn’t apprehensive about this purchase until I opened the box. The west shelving seemed a bit flimsy but I decided to trust the process.1. Very lightweight shipping box and so was the shelf2. Very easy to put together - even without the instructions. I know people aren’t happy with the clarity of the instructions but honestly, it would be hard to mess this up. It took me 35 minutes and the hardest part was slipping the shelving sleeves on the poles. But a mallet does come in handy for making sure everything is tight and secure.3 pleasantly surprised with how sturdy it felt once together. Is holding my kids gaming units just fine.4. Overall for the price, good shelf. Would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great for storage but missing pieces
reviews.reviewText: I ordered 2 of these to reorganize my craft room. While putting it together one plastic bar really snapped while putting the metal cross bar in it. That same box was missing the 5 fabric dividers. I made it work anyways. I do love all the extra space it gives. The shelves are pretty sturdy and are large and can hold a lot. I would have given a 5 star if the above didn’t happen. Overall I am happy with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You get what you pay for
reviews.reviewText: This is 5/5 for being 25$. It's a 25$ piece of furniture, not incredibly sturdy but if you're storing a couple book, fidgets toys, action figures, you'll be good. Of course it's not going to hold a bunch of heavy stuff. The instructions weren't amazing but I can't believe some people can't figure it out. Definitely not rocket science. Took me about 15-20 minutes to put together

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars A big pain.
reviews.reviewText: The product may work, it's unknown. The instructions are certainly lacking, and so is the ability for it to remain together. The front eases apart after the side and back are on. The long section needs to stretch some. Gorilla glue is recommended actually by me if you choose to keep it. It is not hard to put together, but I would suggest GLUE during the construction of this "book case". It sure helps out, believe me. It may be sturdy, the idea is there, but what do you expect for the price?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy piece for the price
reviews.reviewText: It’s a little time consuming….intimidating when you open the box, but not too bad once you start putting it together. Took about an hour. Decent piece for the price, and seems pretty sturdy. It does not come with anything to lag it to the wall, so I did add a couple of brackets, considering I’m using it in a child’s room.Helpful hint - slide the bars into the material pieces before placing them in the holes. Made it go quicker once I started doing it that way. You will want to use a mallet.

Es algo difícil de armar pero queda resistente y le caben muchas cosas. Si se distribuye bien el peso dejando lo más ligero en la parte de arriba queda muy estable. Se puede armar dándome las distintas formas que vienen en las imágenes pero ya no es posible poner el plástico del fondo, por su tamaño solo alcanza a cubrir dos cuadros.

reviews.reviewTitle: Holds a lot and low profile
reviews.reviewText: Definatly a good value. Light weight so anyone can move these around but they are relatively sturdy once assembled and packed. The assembly takes some time and a bit of strength to snap the pieces into place. Because you kind of have to force it, if you aren't lined up perfectly that force may snap a section or slip and cut you. I'd suggest long sleeves to protect yourself if possible. Once it's assembled they are awesome and hold a lot of weight! Got two on sale and would repurchase.
